AB  -  INTERVENTION: Intervention 1: Dekristol (ATC A11CC05, colecalciferol), PO (capsule), for 84 days. Individualized loading dose based on individual 25‐hydroxyvitamin D levels and BMI (20,000 or 40,000 IU daily on day 1 to 11, in sum, on average approx. 180,000 IU) followed by a maintenance dose of 2,000 IU daily for the remaining days. Intervention 2: Control: Placebo for 84 days CONDITION: C18 ‐ Malignant neoplasm of colon C19 ‐ Malignant neoplasm of rectosigmoid junction C20 ‐ Malignant neoplasm of rectum C21 ‐ Malignant neoplasm of anus and anal canal E55 ‐ Vitamin D deficiency Fatigue, tumor‐associated # Quality of life J00‐J06 ‐ Acute upper respiratory infections J20‐J22 ‐ Other acute lower respiratory infections PRIMARY OUTCOME: Mean difference in FACIT‐F fatigue subscale between intervention and placebo group in week 13 to 16. A mean difference = 3 FACIT‐F fatigue subscale points will be considered a clinically relevant difference. INCLUSION CRITERIA: â€¢ Age = 18 years â€¢ Non‐metastatic CRC patients stage I‐III â€¢ Within 9 months after surgical removal of the tumor â€¢ At least 3 weeks of in‐patient rehabilitation in cooperating clinic is planned â€¢ Sufficient knowledge of the German language and mental capabilities to be able to give written informed consent and comply with the study requirements SECONDARY OUTCOME: â€¢ Mean difference in change of FACIT‐F fatigue subscale from baseline to trial week 13‐16 between intervention and placebo group. A mean difference = 3 FACIT‐F fatigue subscale points will be considered a clinically relevant difference.; â€¢ Mean differences in EORTC‐FA12 physical, emotional and cognitive fatigue scores between intervention and placebo group at trial week 13‐16 as well as mean differences in changes in these scores from baseline to trial week 13‐16 between intervention and placebo group.; â€¢ Mean difference in GDS‐15 depression scale between intervention and placebo group at trial week 13‐16 as well as mean difference 